--- @target: std.collections
Collection types including Queue, Stack, Grid2D, PriorityQueue, CircularBuffer, BTreeMap, BTreeSet, and Grid3D.
---

--- @target: queue_int_new
Creates a new empty queue of integers using a list internally with FIFO semantics.
@return An empty queue.
---

--- @target: queue_int_enqueue
Adds an integer to the back of the queue.
@param queue The queue to enqueue into.
@param value The integer value to add.
@return A new queue with the value appended.
---

--- @target: queue_int_dequeue
Removes and returns the integer at the front of the queue.
@param queue The queue to dequeue from.
@return The front value wrapped in @link optional, or none if empty.
---

--- @target: queue_int_peek
Returns the integer at the front of the queue without removing it.
@param queue The queue to peek at.
@return The front value wrapped in @link optional, or none if empty.
---

--- @target: queue_text_new
Creates a new empty queue of text using a list internally with FIFO semantics.
@return An empty text queue.
---

--- @target: queue_text_enqueue
Adds text to the back of the queue.
@param queue The queue to enqueue into.
@param value The text value to add.
@return A new queue with the value appended.
---

--- @target: queue_text_dequeue
Removes and returns the text at the front of the queue.
@param queue The queue to dequeue from.
@return The front value wrapped in @link optional, or none if empty.
---

--- @target: queue_text_peek
Returns the text at the front of the queue without removing it.
@param queue The queue to peek at.
@return The front value wrapped in @link optional, or none if empty.
---

--- @target: stack_int_new
Creates a new empty stack of integers using a list internally with LIFO semantics.
@return An empty stack.
---

--- @target: stack_int_push
Pushes an integer onto the top of the stack.
@param stack The stack to push onto.
@param value The integer value to push.
@return A new stack with the value on top.
---

--- @target: stack_int_pop
Removes and returns the integer at the top of the stack.
@param stack The stack to pop from.
@return The top value wrapped in @link optional, or none if empty.
---

--- @target: stack_int_peek
Returns the integer at the top of the stack without removing it.
@param stack The stack to peek at.
@return The top value wrapped in @link optional, or none if empty.
---

--- @target: stack_text_new
Creates a new empty stack of text using a list internally with LIFO semantics.
@return An empty text stack.
---

--- @target: stack_text_push
Pushes text onto the top of the stack.
@param stack The stack to push onto.
@param value The text value to push.
@return A new stack with the value on top.
---

--- @target: stack_text_pop
Removes and returns the text at the top of the stack.
@param stack The stack to pop from.
@return The top value wrapped in @link optional, or none if empty.
---

--- @target: stack_text_peek
Returns the text at the top of the stack without removing it.
@param stack The stack to peek at.
@return The top value wrapped in @link optional, or none if empty.
---

--- @target: grid2d_int_new
Creates a new 2D grid of integers with the specified dimensions.

@param rows Number of rows.
@param cols Number of columns.
@return A new grid initialized with zero values.
---

--- @target: grid2d_int_get
Gets the integer value at the specified grid coordinates.

@param grid The grid to read from.
@param row The row index (0-based).
@param col The column index (0-based).
@return The value at the specified position.
---

--- @target: grid2d_int_set
Sets the integer value at the specified grid coordinates.

@param grid The grid to modify.
@param row The row index (0-based).
@param col The column index (0-based).
@param value The new value.
@return A new grid with the value set (uses copy-on-write).
---

--- @target: grid2d_int_fill
Fills the entire grid with a single integer value.

@param grid The grid to fill.
@param value The value to fill with.
@return A new grid with all cells set to value.
---

--- @target: grid2d_int_rows
Returns the number of rows in the grid.

@param grid The grid to query.
@return The row count.
---

--- @target: grid2d_int_cols
Returns the number of columns in the grid.

@param grid The grid to query.
@return The column count.
---

--- @target: grid2d_text_new
Creates a new 2D grid of text with the specified dimensions.

@param rows Number of rows.
@param cols Number of columns.
@return A new grid initialized with empty text values.
---

--- @target: grid2d_text_get
Gets the text value at the specified grid coordinates.

@param grid The grid to read from.
@param row The row index (0-based).
@param col The column index (0-based).
@return The value at the specified position.
---

--- @target: grid2d_text_set
Sets the text value at the specified grid coordinates.

@param grid The grid to modify.
@param row The row index (0-based).
@param col The column index (0-based).
@param value The new text value.
@return A new grid with the value set (uses copy-on-write).
---

--- @target: grid2d_text_fill
Fills the entire grid with a single text value.

@param grid The grid to fill.
@param value The text value to fill with.
@return A new grid with all cells set to value.
---

--- @target: grid2d_text_rows
Returns the number of rows in the text grid.

@param grid The grid to query.
@return The row count.
---

--- @target: grid2d_text_cols
Returns the number of columns in the text grid.

@param grid The grid to query.
@return The column count.
---

--- @target: pqueue_int_new
Creates a new empty minimum priority queue of integers.
@return An empty priority queue.
---

--- @target: pqueue_int_push
Inserts an integer into the priority queue.

@param heap The priority queue to insert into.
@param value The integer value to insert.
@return A new priority queue with the value inserted.
---

--- @target: pqueue_int_pop
Removes and returns the smallest integer from the priority queue.

@param heap The priority queue to pop from.
@return The smallest value wrapped in @link optional, or none if empty.
---

--- @target: pqueue_int_peek
Returns the smallest integer without removing it from the priority queue.

@param heap The priority queue to peek at.
@return The smallest value wrapped in @link optional, or none if empty.
---

--- @target: pqueue_int_len
Returns the number of elements in the integer priority queue.

@param heap The priority queue to query.
@return The element count.
---

--- @target: pqueue_text_new
Creates a new empty minimum priority queue of text.
@return An empty text priority queue.
---

--- @target: pqueue_text_push
Inserts text into the priority queue using lexicographic ordering.

@param heap The priority queue to insert into.
@param value The text value to insert.
@return A new priority queue with the value inserted.
---

--- @target: pqueue_text_pop
Removes and returns the smallest text from the priority queue.

@param heap The priority queue to pop from.
@return The smallest value wrapped in @link optional, or none if empty.
---

--- @target: pqueue_text_peek
Returns the smallest text without removing it from the priority queue.

@param heap The priority queue to peek at.
@return The smallest value wrapped in @link optional, or none if empty.
---

--- @target: pqueue_text_len
Returns the number of elements in the text priority queue.

@param heap The priority queue to query.
@return The element count.
---

--- @target: circbuf_int_new
Creates a new circular buffer of integers with a fixed capacity.

@param capacity The maximum number of elements the buffer can hold.
@return A new circular buffer with the specified capacity.
---

--- @target: circbuf_int_push
Pushes an integer into the circular buffer. If the buffer is full, the oldest element is overwritten.

@param buf The circular buffer to push into.
@param value The integer value to push.
@return A new circular buffer with the value added.
---

--- @target: circbuf_int_pop
Removes and returns the oldest integer from the circular buffer.

@param buf The circular buffer to pop from.
@return The oldest value wrapped in @link optional, or none if empty.
---

--- @target: circbuf_int_peek
Returns the oldest integer without removing it from the circular buffer.

@param buf The circular buffer to peek at.
@return The oldest value wrapped in @link optional, or none if empty.
---

--- @target: circbuf_int_len
Returns the current number of elements in the circular buffer.

@param buf The circular buffer to query.
@return The element count (between 0 and capacity).
---

--- @target: circbuf_int_capacity
Returns the maximum capacity of the circular buffer.

@param buf The circular buffer to query.
@return The capacity.
---

--- @target: circbuf_int_is_full
Checks whether the circular buffer is at full capacity.

@param buf The circular buffer to check.
@return True if the buffer is full.
---

--- @target: circbuf_text_new
Creates a new circular buffer of text with a fixed capacity.

@param capacity The maximum number of elements the buffer can hold.
@return A new text circular buffer with the specified capacity.
---

--- @target: circbuf_text_push
Pushes text into the circular buffer. If the buffer is full, the oldest element is overwritten.

@param buf The circular buffer to push into.
@param value The text value to push.
@return A new circular buffer with the value added.
---

--- @target: circbuf_text_pop
Removes and returns the oldest text from the circular buffer.

@param buf The circular buffer to pop from.
@return The oldest value wrapped in @link optional, or none if empty.
---

--- @target: circbuf_text_peek
Returns the oldest text without removing it from the circular buffer.

@param buf The circular buffer to peek at.
@return The oldest value wrapped in @link optional, or none if empty.
---

--- @target: circbuf_text_len
Returns the current number of elements in the text circular buffer.

@param buf The circular buffer to query.
@return The element count.
---

--- @target: circbuf_text_capacity
Returns the maximum capacity of the text circular buffer.

@param buf The circular buffer to query.
@return The capacity.
---

--- @target: circbuf_text_is_full
Checks whether the text circular buffer is at full capacity.

@param buf The circular buffer to check.
@return True if the buffer is full.
---

--- @target: btreemap_text_new
Creates a new empty ordered map from text keys to text values.

@return An empty BTreeMap.
---

--- @target: btreemap_text_set
Inserts or updates a key-value pair in the map.

@param self_map The map to modify.
@param key The text key.
@param value The text value.
@return A new map with the key set (uses copy-on-write).
---

--- @target: btreemap_text_get
Retrieves the value associated with a key.

@param self_map The map to query.
@param key The text key to look up.
@return The associated value.
---

--- @target: btreemap_text_get_optional
Retrieves the value associated with a key, or none if the key is not present.

@param self_map The map to query.
@param key The text key to look up.
@return The value wrapped in @link optional, or none if not found.
---

--- @target: btreemap_text_contains
Checks whether a key exists in the map.

@param self_map The map to query.
@param key The text key to check.
@return True if the key is present.
---

--- @target: btreemap_text_remove
Removes a key-value pair from the map.

@param self_map The map to modify.
@param key The text key to remove.
@return A new map with the key removed.
---

--- @target: btreemap_text_len
Returns the number of key-value pairs in the map.

@param self_map The map to query.
@return The pair count.
---

--- @target: btreeset_text_new
Creates a new empty ordered set of text values.
@return An empty BTreeSet.
---

--- @target: btreeset_text_insert
Inserts a value into the set.

@param set The set to modify.
@param value The text value to insert.
@return A new set with the value inserted.
---

--- @target: btreeset_text_contains
Checks whether a value exists in the set.

@param set The set to query.
@param value The text value to check.
@return True if the value is present.
---

--- @target: btreeset_text_remove
Removes a value from the set.

@param set The set to modify.
@param value The text value to remove.
@return A new set with the value removed.
---

--- @target: btreeset_text_len
Returns the number of values in the set.

@param set The set to query.
@return The value count.
---

--- @target: grid3d_int_new
Creates a new 3D grid of integers with the specified dimensions.

@param depth Number of layers (depth).
@param rows Number of rows per layer.
@param cols Number of columns per layer.
@return A new 3D grid initialized with zero values.
---

--- @target: grid3d_int_get
Gets the integer value at the specified 3D coordinates.

@param grid The 3D grid to read from.
@param layer The layer index (0-based).
@param row The row index (0-based).
@param col The column index (0-based).
@return The value at the specified position.
---

--- @target: grid3d_int_set
Sets the integer value at the specified 3D coordinates.

@param grid The 3D grid to modify.
@param layer The layer index (0-based).
@param row The row index (0-based).
@param col The column index (0-based).
@param value The new value.
@return A new 3D grid with the value set (uses copy-on-write).
---

--- @target: grid3d_int_fill
Fills the entire 3D grid with a single integer value.

@param grid The 3D grid to fill.
@param value The value to fill with.
@return A new 3D grid with all cells set to value.
---

--- @target: grid3d_int_depth
Returns the number of layers in the 3D grid.

@param grid The 3D grid to query.
@return The depth (layer count).
---

--- @target: grid3d_int_rows
Returns the number of rows per layer in the 3D grid.

@param grid The 3D grid to query.
@return The row count.
---

--- @target: grid3d_int_cols
Returns the number of columns per layer in the 3D grid.

@param grid The 3D grid to query.
@return The column count.
---

--- @target: grid3d_text_new
Creates a new 3D grid of text with the specified dimensions.

@param depth Number of layers (depth).
@param rows Number of rows per layer.
@param cols Number of columns per layer.
@return A new 3D text grid initialized with empty text values.
---

--- @target: grid3d_text_get
Gets the text value at the specified 3D coordinates.

@param grid The 3D grid to read from.
@param layer The layer index (0-based).
@param row The row index (0-based).
@param col The column index (0-based).
@return The value at the specified position.
---

--- @target: grid3d_text_set
Sets the text value at the specified 3D coordinates.

@param grid The 3D grid to modify.
@param layer The layer index (0-based).
@param row The row index (0-based).
@param col The column index (0-based).
@param value The new text value.
@return A new 3D grid with the value set (uses copy-on-write).
---

--- @target: grid3d_text_fill
Fills the entire 3D text grid with a single text value.

@param grid The 3D grid to fill.
@param value The text value to fill with.
@return A new 3D grid with all cells set to value.
---

--- @target: grid3d_text_depth
Returns the number of layers in the 3D text grid.

@param grid The 3D grid to query.
@return The depth (layer count).
---

--- @target: grid3d_text_rows
Returns the number of rows per layer in the 3D text grid.

@param grid The 3D grid to query.
@return The row count.
---

--- @target: grid3d_text_cols
Returns the number of columns per layer in the 3D text grid.

@param grid The 3D grid to query.
@return The column count.
---

--- @target: pqueue_int_is_empty
Checks whether the integer priority queue has no elements.

@param heap The priority queue to check.
@return True if the queue is empty.
---

--- @target: pqueue_text_is_empty
Checks whether the text priority queue has no elements.

@param heap The priority queue to check.
@return True if the queue is empty.
---

--- @target: circbuf_int_is_empty
Checks whether the integer circular buffer has no elements.

@param buf The circular buffer to check.
@return True if the buffer is empty.
---

--- @target: circbuf_text_is_empty
Checks whether the text circular buffer has no elements.

@param buf The circular buffer to check.
@return True if the buffer is empty.
---

--- @target: btreemap_text_is_empty
Checks whether the BTreeMap has no key-value pairs.

@param self_map The map to check.
@return True if the map is empty.
---

--- @target: btreeset_text_is_empty
Checks whether the BTreeSet has no values.

@param set The set to check.
@return True if the set is empty.
---

--- @target: grid2d_int_size
Returns the total number of cells in the 2D integer grid (rows * cols).

@param grid The grid to query.
@return The total cell count.
---

--- @target: grid2d_text_size
Returns the total number of cells in the 2D text grid (rows * cols).

@param grid The grid to query.
@return The total cell count.
---

--- @target: grid3d_int_size
Returns the total number of cells in the 3D integer grid (depth * rows * cols).

@param grid The 3D grid to query.
@return The total cell count.
---

--- @target: grid3d_text_size
Returns the total number of cells in the 3D text grid (depth * rows * cols).

@param grid The 3D grid to query.
@return The total cell count.
---
